description: From Latin ēmūnctus, past participle of ēmungō (“to blow one's nose”) + -ory.

adjectives.description: emunctory (comparative more emunctory, superlative most emunctory)

entries.meaning: Pertaining to the elimination of waste from the body.
examples: A mixture of poor diet and poor hygiene caused him inflammation of the emunctory aperture.

entries.meaning: Any part of the body which carries or removes waste.
